Assistant Teaching Professor
Department of Computer Science and Engineering
Email: szs339@psu.edu

  • Ashwin Senthil Arumugam
  • MD Amit Hasan Arovi

Office Hours

Monday Tuesday Wednesday Thursday Friday

Dr. Suman Saha

Location: W109F Westgate Building

 2:00 PM - 3:00 PM 9:00 AM - 10:00 AM

Neeraj Karamchandani

Location: Westgate W136

 11:00 AM - 12:00 PM

Ashwin Senthil Arumugam

Location: Westgate W136

 4:00 PM - 5:00 PM

MD Amit Hasan Arovi

Location: 300W building

 4:00 PM - 5:00 PM 9:00 AM - 10:00 AM

Course Objectives:

This course explores programming and computation ii concepts and methodologies. Students will gain hands-on experience through lectures, programming assignments, and projects.

Grading

Activity Percentage
Course Projects 50%
Midterm Exams 30%
Final Exam 20%

Academic Integrity Statement

The course projects are to be carried out individually. Students are explicitly not allowed to share information, source code, or even discuss the contents of the projects. Any violation of this policy will be considered cheating and will result in the student receiving an 'F' grade for the project.

Lateness Policy

Lab assignments are assessed a 10% per day late penalty, up to a maximum of three days after which a zero grade will be given.

courses.syllabus_body:
ACCTG 301 Intermediate Accounting

Course Description

The objective of this course is to introduce students to the discipline of accounting. This course provides students with an understanding of accounting information and how it is used by various decision-makers.

announcements.title: Final Project Presentations
announcements.message:
Final Project Presentations will be held during the last week of class.

Presentation Schedule:

  • Each team will have 10 minutes to present
  • 5 minutes for questions and discussion
  • All team members must participate

Presentation Requirements:

  • Demonstrate your working solution
  • Explain your design decisions
  • Discuss challenges and solutions

Detailed rubric will be posted soon.
